			<p>In the modern world, humans <textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE6" /><strong>(not/stay)</strong> in one place anymore, and so new viruses also <textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE7" /><strong>(travel)</strong> more easily. When humans <textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE8" /><strong>(visit)</strong> different regions (for example, Africa), they <textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE9" /><strong>(not/realize)</strong> how easy it is to bring a new kind of disease back with them.</p>

